UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I see your commitment and that you have understood what I have taught you, $N.' WHERE entry=6101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Understanding the balance between nature and oneself is a way of life for every $R.' WHERE entry=6101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have learned all I can teach you, $N. May I offer you one more piece of advice: use discretion when choosing your first pet. Will you choose a creature of the land, of the water, or of the sky? Whatever it may be, without doubt, your pet will be with you for quite some time.$B$BHere you are, $N. I will now give you the power to tame a beast, as well as call it and dismiss it as you see fit. Use your new skills with pride; you have earned them.' WHERE entry=6102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='I am proud of your accomplishments, $N. Have you finished the last task I gave you?' WHERE entry=6102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A fledgling $C. I see. Yes. I can bestow you with the skills you need to train and guide your pet. Not only will you be able to teach your pet new abilities, you will now be able to feed your pet, as well as revive it, should it fall in battle.$B$BRemember, $N, always respect the balance and live in awe of nature around you. Now, go forth. We shall speak again, at a later date.' WHERE entry=6103;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Greetings young $C, I\'m glad to see you ready and eager to learn about the curing of poisons.$B$BWhile most druids in the past were put through pre-planned trials, your work will involve no such thing. There has been a rash of animal poisonings in Auberdine, and the village there has been unable to cure it. To that end, a representative there has asked Moonglade for aid and we are sending you there to aid them. This is no exercise - the work you\'ll do is quite real. Bear this in mind.' WHERE entry=6121;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='By Elune, this water is disgusting! No wonder the deer are sick.$B$BSomething is polluting the water, and in turn corrupting Darkshore\'s entire water table. Sick deer have been seen all over area, and not just by the river. While this water is most likely a primary source of the sickness spreading, there\'s something else at work here.$B$BThis water, believe it or not, will help us formulate a cure. While I research this water, I have need of some items to formulate a cure...' WHERE entry=6122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is good, $N, so much so that it should be enough to make some ample doses of the salve - at least enough to start to make a difference.$B$BMaking a cure for poisons can be quite difficult at times because each one often requires a very specific antidote to counteract it. Imagine being able to cure a poison at will without having to worry about the exact ingredients of what the antidote must be!$B$BNow, let me get to work on this!' WHERE entry=6123;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done well in tending to the sickly deer of Darkshore; they are unwitting victims of a greater taint and corruption that is spreading all throughout the land.  There are those in Darnassus who choose to recognize this threat... and there are those who ignore the growing signs.  I hope you will not be one to put blinders on about what facts stare you in the face, $N.$B$BRegardless, you\'ve proven your worth as a friend of nature and the Circle - take this as a symbol of such.' WHERE entry=6124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Welcome back - I\'ve been following your progress on this lesson since you left, and I must admit I was surprised to learn about the situation in Auberdine.  This does bear some further investigation, as the introduction of such poisons into the environment is most upsetting to the balance.$B$BYou handled yourself with grace under pressure.  For that, I can find no better way to reward you than with permanent power over poison.  Use it well, $N... use it well.' WHERE entry=6125;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Greetings young druid, I\'m glad to see you ready and eager to learn about the curing of poisons.$B$BWhile most druids in the past were put through pre-planned trials, your work will involve no such thing. There has been a rash of animal poisonings at the Crossroads in the Barrens, and they\'re unable to bring it under control. Someone there has requested Moonglade for aid, so we are sending you there to aid them. This is no exercise - the work you\'ll do is quite real. Bear this in mind.' WHERE entry=6126;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='By my ancestors, this water is disgusting! No wonder the gazelles are sick.$B$BSomething is polluting the water, and in turn beginning to wreck the northern Barrens ecosystem. Sick gazelles have been sighted all north of the east-west road here. While this water is most likely a primary source of the sickness spreading, there\'s something else at work here.$B$BThis water, believe it or not, will help us formulate a cure. While I research this water, I have need of some items to formulate a cure...' WHERE entry=6127;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is good, $N, so much so that it should be enough to make some ample doses of the salve - at least enough to start to make a difference.$B$BMaking a cure for poisons can be quite difficult at times because each one often requires a very specific antidote to counteract it. Imagine being able to cure a poison at will without having to worry about the exact ingredients of what the antidote must be!$B$BNow, let me get to work on this!' WHERE entry=6128;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done well in tending to the sickly gazelles of the Barrens; they are unwitting victims of a greater taint and corruption that is spreading all throughout the land. You $R are most eager to understand the ways of Cenarius; you, like your elders in Thunder Bluff, are proving that the need for balance transcends artificial racial barriers.$B$B$N, you\'ve proven your worth as an friend of nature and the Circle - take this as a symbol of such.' WHERE entry=6129;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Welcome back - I\'ve been following your progress on this lesson since you left, and I must admit I was surprised to learn about the situation at the Crossroads. This does bear some further investigation, as the introduction of such poisons into the environment is most upsetting to the balance.$B$BYou handled yourself with grace under pressure. For that, I can find no better way to reward you with permanent power over poison. Use it well, $N... use it well.' WHERE entry=6130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='We suffer much from the events of the past. Thank you for what you have done to help protect the Timbermaw.' WHERE entry=6131;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='My sister Melizza said you\'d be coming.  Thanks a lot for getting her out of the jam she was in; it\'s too bad that she\'s already probably found herself in a new one!' WHERE entry=6132;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I trust you did not read the registry. Not even you would do something that idiotic...' WHERE entry=6133;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There it is!  Looks like you got some of it on you too.  Kinda slimey, eh?$B$BWell, thanks a lot for all the trouble, $N.  This stuff will be worth a fortune... if I can convince the centaurs what it is!' WHERE entry=6134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, imbecile. I shall fashion this fur into something you can use.$B$B' WHERE entry=6135;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Keep this up and I may have to promote you from imbecile to mental deficient, first class.' WHERE entry=6136;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I received word of aid arriving from the east.  Are you the source of these rumors?  Have you come here to help the Scarlet Brother in its crusade?$B$BIf so, then listen close...' WHERE entry=6141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Perfect mon, this is just what the witch doctor told me to do for my headache. He says, ""Mai\'Lahii - go fish. It\'ll make you feel better""$B$BWell, I feel better already, thanks mon!' WHERE entry=6142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='As sweet as it is hearing the news that the naga have been vanquished, my heart still feels empty. For the rest of my life I will be dedicated to having them all killed.$B$BHere mon, your reward as I promised. It\'s small in comparison to the gratification of knowing the naga fried for their hated act upon my crew.' WHERE entry=6143;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The Grand Crusader sits safely in the Scarlet Bastion while his forces pour into your lands, desecrate your structures and monuments and murder your people.$B$BThe Dark Lady has commanded that I deal with this insect once and for all. You will become the instrument of the Forsaken\'s reckoning.' WHERE entry=6144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Nathanos laughs.>$B$BExcellent! Finally! An opportunity to destroy the Scarlet Oracle!' WHERE entry=6145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Where have you been? We had thought the Scourge had captured you.' WHERE entry=6146;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The fools! My deception went unnoticed! Prepare yourself, $C. We must strike with cold cunning!' WHERE entry=6147;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='They will be reeling from this blow for years! Well done, $N! You have earned not only my respect but also this reward.' WHERE entry=6148;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Chest opens to reveal Rackmore\'s treasure!' WHERE entry=6161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You bring honor to me for following through with your word. My husband died in battle--he would have been proud of that. But I could not rest until I knew that the creature that has forced me to live my life alone paid for what it had done.$B$BThank you again, $N.' WHERE entry=6162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Ramstein',offerrewardtext_loc2='I wonder... did it beg for mercy? Could it know what mercy is?$B$B<Nathanos spits.>$B$BI will hang this beast\'s head upon my wall.$B$BYou have earned a spot amongst one of my champions, $N.$B$B<Nathanos salutes.>' WHERE entry=6163;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There it is! And oh my! I forgot how full it was!$B$BThis is a glorious day, $N! Stupendous! Insanely good, I say!' WHERE entry=6164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have to get this note to Stormwind? That\'s not a problem, you can take one of my gryphons!' WHERE entry=6181;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='After some reports of unusual Forsaken activity in the Eastern Plaguelands, SI:7 agents were dispatched to investigate. The results of that investigation are unsettling.' WHERE entry=6182;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Mathias nods.>$B$BI had faith that Bolvar would send me men and women of honor - the most dedicated soldiers of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=6183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The first mission will be straight up, $N. You go in, you come out. Recon...' WHERE entry=6184;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Rutger. Fredo. Turyen. All... dead...$B$B<Flint clutches the insignias tightly.>$B$BWhere were they? Did you discover any more information about this bastard, the Blightcaller?' WHERE entry=6185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='An... Any luck??' WHERE entry=6185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='No. It... NO! How? An agent of the Forsaken? The CHAMPION of the Banshee Queen???$B$B<Highlord Bolvar Fordragon slumps in defeat.>' WHERE entry=6186;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It is a tragedy. I think... I believe that our kind is cursed, $N. We are cursed to lose our greatest warriors; our most noble heroes; our most gifted scholars.$B$BWe are indebted to you and I assure you, $N, wherever Nathanos Marris is now, he smiles down upon you.' WHERE entry=6187;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thank you for what you have done. Please continue to help us, $N. We have very few allies on which to call upon.' WHERE entry=6241;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A crate for Westfall, eh? Have you been to Westall before? If so, then it\'s no problem, my friend. I have plenty of gryphons trained to fly that route!' WHERE entry=6261;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, a note from Quartermaster Lewis? I\'m not surprised he needs more gear. Sentinel Hill is far away, in a land Stormwind has all but forgotten.$B$BWell thank you, $N. Here\'s some money to cover your travel costs.' WHERE entry=6281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is most excellent news! Tell me again how you cast fear into the cold hearts of those vile harpies. The Bloodfuries have been dealt a serious blow!' WHERE entry=6282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Already I feel the anger leave me. What will I do with my time? Knowing evil moves near my land kept my thoughts moving, though now they are silent. Perhaps this is a good thing... maybe now I can focus on the good, as all Tauren should.$B$BPlease accept this as a reward for your troubles.' WHERE entry=6283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Good hunting, $N! Besseleth is an old predator in these parts... I will miss her not. Take this reward as a token for being the forest champion.$B$B<Maggran rubs the wound caused by Besseleth.>$B$BPerhaps now many more will travel to Sun Rock Retreat without fearing what lurks in the dark.' WHERE entry=6284;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Great, you brought the armor! We\'ll get this divvied to those who need it immediately.$B$BThank you, $N. Your efforts have been a great help to us. And now that you\'re no stranger to gryphons, I hope you\'ll come and lend your aid to Sentinel Hill often!' WHERE entry=6285;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah? $N, you have the Gaea seeds. Watch and you shall see the power that these seeds will do for the land. Only those pure and true can heal the land?$B$B<Tammra begins to chant.>' WHERE entry=6301;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, an order for supplies.  You will want to take this to the Undercity, no doubt.  And quickly, for the Sepulcher must not be left under stocked.' WHERE entry=6321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Michael Garrett',offerrewardtext_loc2='This crate must reach the Sepulcher in Silverpine? That is easily done; our bats fly there daily.' WHERE entry=6322;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='An order from the Sepulcher? Very well. It is an honor to serve those who serve our Dark Lady.' WHERE entry=6323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Good work, $N. These weapons will ensure our Deathguards don\'t get caught unprepared.$B$BYou have done a valuable service for our Dark Lady.' WHERE entry=6324;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, you wish to get this to Auberdine? Very well...' WHERE entry=6341;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A package from Nessa? Thank you, $N! She told me she would send me samples of the fish caught near Rut\'theran village. She thinks they may be very different from the fish caught here...$B$BMy! This jawbone is nearly twice the size of the same fish found here. And these scales are as big as a closed fist! Amazing!' WHERE entry=6342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is very interesting. The fish here are large, but I didn\'t think the difference in bounties between here and the mainland was so great. There must be a reason for this...$B$BWell thank you, $N. I will discuss with the villagers the news you brought. Perhaps, one day, we will find the root of this oddity. But until then, we shall reap its benefits!' WHERE entry=6343;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Yes, I have need of a courier who will take a package to Darkshore. Will you help me?' WHERE entry=6344;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='If you must take these hides to Thunder Bluff, then you are speaking to the right orc!' WHERE entry=6361;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, a new bundle of hides. I will get to work on these immediately!$B$BThank you, brother. You have done me a great service. Here are some coins to pay for your time and travel costs.' WHERE entry=6362;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You need to take this to the Crossroads, eh? That\'s not a problem. If you\'ve already been there and spoken to Devrak, then you can take one of my wind riders back to him.' WHERE entry=6363;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ahanu sent me finished products? Very good. There are many hunters and adventurers in the Crossroads now and business is lively. I am sure I\'ll sell these goods very soon.$B$BThank you for all your efforts, $N. I am in your debt.' WHERE entry=6364;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have to get this meat to Orgrimmar? That is no problem. For a small fee, my wind rider can take you there.' WHERE entry=6365;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is great victory for the land. In time, other things will come to pass: the Venture Co. will pack up their buzz saws and axes, the angry fire spirits will calm, and the harpies will be pushed out by the land.$B$BOnly then $N, will Stonetalon be truly at peace.$B$BYou have done well $C; take one of these items as thanks for the new life you have created here today.' WHERE entry=6381;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Welcome to the new frontier, $N.  Ashenvale is a land of opportunity, one where a young $C like yourself is able to find boundless chances to prove their mettle.  Look around the outpost here, and be sure to travel out to the Zoram Strand, as the Horde has another outpost there as well.$B$BYour presence here tells me that you\'ve come to learn more about the hunt.  Listen close, and I will gladly share with you what you need to know.' WHERE entry=6382;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There are three legendary creatures that make up the Ashenvale Hunt; you may seek them and test yourself against their cunning and might.  In the process, you will hopefully learn something about yourself.  The creatures are: the bear Ursangous, the nightsaber cat Shadumbra, and the hippogryph Sharptalon.$B$BThe creatures of the Ashenvale Hunt are powerful, and you may find that you\'ll need aid in bringing them down.  If you should best them, bring me proof of your deed.' WHERE entry=6383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh, wonderful! Those are fine cuts! These are from Zargh, are they? That orc sure knows his way into a lady\'s heart...$B$BOh, I can\'t wait to cook it. But not too much! Meat is best served rare, don\'t you think?' WHERE entry=6384;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have to get this to the Crossroads in the Barrens? Yes, I can get you there...' WHERE entry=6385;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hah! I guess she liked it! Nothing brings red to a lady\'s cheeks like a big, juicy steak!$B$BThank you, $N. You\'ve done me a great service. Here is some money for your trouble, and don\'t be surprised if I invite you to my wedding!' WHERE entry=6386;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have to get this to Ironforge, eh? For a small fee I can put you on the back of one of my gryphons, and it\'ll take you there. How does that sound?' WHERE entry=6387;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Gryth Thurden',offerrewardtext_loc2='You have to get these to Thelsamar, eh? That won\'t be a problem. As long as you\'ve already been to Thelsamar and spoken to Thorgrum Borrelson, then you can take one of my gryphons back to him.' WHERE entry=6388;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Haha! Thank you, $N! You\'ve done it! My father\'s spirit can now rest and I can live in peace.$B$BThank you again. If there is anything I can do for you, please, just ask.' WHERE entry=6389;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thank you, $N. Here, take this coin. I\'m sorry it\'s not more, but try to take some joy in helping destroy the Scarlet Crusade\'s efforts!' WHERE entry=6390;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, the lastest list of Brock\'s best pupils. I have a batch of honorary picks ready to go. I just need to chisel in the names of the students...' WHERE entry=6391;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You brought the picks. Great! I\'ll get these to my mining students. I\'m sure they\'re eager to use them on the ore deposits of Loch Modan.$B$BThank you for your help, $N. I am in your debt, but I hope this money will at least cover your travel costs.' WHERE entry=6392;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The water spirits within me bubble with the excitement. $N, you have given me a glorious victory to report to the Tribunal of the Tides.$B$BFor your efforts, I reward you with a choice of my prized possessions.' WHERE entry=6393;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Great, you got it! Thanks a lot, $N. This is my favorite pick! Now if my peons ever finish chopping down these trees, maybe we can find a nice cave to mine!' WHERE entry=6394;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done a good deed today, $N. Although our struggle against the Scourge continues, let us hope that Marla and Samuel will find peace together in their final resting place.' WHERE entry=6395;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='My goodness, my niece Kaya is alive! That is good news indeed. Thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=6401;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Before we begin, I ask that you first gather an army. We face a dragon, after all!' WHERE entry=6402;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Bolvar holds the shattered medallion.>$B$BThe magic held within must be reignited. The dragon\'s eye must be attuned.$B$BWindsor\'s sacrifice has freed our Kingdom, but the threat of Onyxia and her kin is ever looming.$B$BThis medallion is what held my mind and body captive. It is also what gave me access to Onyxia\'s own mind - to her secrets. Albeit the visions are muddled now, some things I do remember.' WHERE entry=6403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='I... I... I was powerless.' WHERE entry=6403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah... Yes! That\'s it; the Resonite crystals have a trace of Earthen magic. The Kobolds must have dug deep uncovering an Earthen.$B$BLegend states that the Earthen are creatures created by the Titans. They were used to create the land our feet walk on. This most definitely is a threat that cannot be ignored.$B$B<Mor\'rogal shakes his head.>$B$BPerhaps I can enchant these ore samples to use against this Kobold plot.' WHERE entry=6421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='What news have you discovered from Boulderslide Ravine? I recall some legend that deals with Resonite... I just cannot place my hoof on it. Perhaps knowing what lies at the bottom of the cave will illuminate their devious intentions.' WHERE entry=6421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These are perfect, $N! Thanks for helping me out!$B$BOh, and this is for your time...' WHERE entry=6441;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='We could use more of your kind around here, $N. Thank you for your help.' WHERE entry=6442;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Sweet, mon! Good news, perhaps we will have fewer unwanted dinner gusts tonight.$B$BAs I said earlier, we are in your debt... maybe you would care for one of these for your deed?' WHERE entry=6461;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You found them! Thank you! Thank you, $N! You do not know how great a thing you have done for me.$B$BA troll without his charm is like an orc without his battle scars...$B$BWorthless.' WHERE entry=6462;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You bear good news, $C! I fear the possibilities of what an Earthen would mean to Kalimdor.$B$BSlaying Goggeroc was a task for no one less then a hero. You have done well; all of Stonetalon and Kalimdor are indebted to you, noble $C.$B$BAccept this as your reward most honored one.' WHERE entry=6481;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You found my brother!  He was captured by the Thistlefurs?  That is terrible news to hear, for although many Furbolgs are noble creatures, the Thistlefurs are corrupt.$B$BThank you for rescuing my brother, $N.  I do not want to think of how they treated poor Ruul.  He will likely sleep long after this ordeal...' WHERE entry=6482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Have you seen my brother Ruul? He walked into the forest days ago and has not returned...' WHERE entry=6482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I should have known - a piece of the black dragon brood mother, Onyxia. How revolting...' WHERE entry=6501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This amulet will grant you the access that you seek. The lair of Onyxia can be found in Dustwallow Marsh. As long as you hold the amulet, her wards cannot prevent you from entering.$B$BThe Blue Flight wishes you luck, $N.' WHERE entry=6502;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Very good, $N. Your hunting skills are impressive...$B$BThe loss of those outrunners help blind the Alliance, and when they lack intelligence they are less likely to launch attacks.' WHERE entry=6503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Reading isn\'t my strong point... but now I\'ll be able to get back to work! Thanks, $N!' WHERE entry=6504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Good. Well done, $C.$B$BNow that Malcin is dead, we can at least know that the Scourges advances will be halted. The Dark Lady thanks you for your efforts and wishes to reward you with a gift.$B$BAlthough we do not know the extent of the Scourges influence within the Downs, I am sure we will discover their plots soon enough.' WHERE entry=6521;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I recognize the insignia on this scroll, $N. You found this on that crone who reigns over Razorfen Kraul? Interesting.$B$BThe Scourge aren\'t content with one continent it seems. This Ambassador Malcin--the one who wrote the note--is one of the Scourge\'s plagued servants, a human diplomat to the kingdom of Lordaeron before things... changed.$B$BIf the Scourge are trying to gain a foothold in Kalimdor, then it is up to us to act.' WHERE entry=6522;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Kaya is alive! $N, I have you to thank for rescuing her.' WHERE entry=6523;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.' WHERE entry=6541;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.' WHERE entry=6542;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I can see that you are one that can be counted on. These updates are crucial to our plans to further our presence in Ashenvale. We can now plan our next move.' WHERE entry=6543;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='So Torek\'s attack was successful! Well done, $N. Night elves are decent foes. A little skinny, but strong and fierce! I\'m sure the battle was something to see...$B$BAnd I hope you gained a scar or two!' WHERE entry=6544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Torek was sent on a mission against Silverwing Outpost. Was the attack successful?' WHERE entry=6544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well, my update will explain all of this to Kadrak. You must return this to him as quickly as possible.' WHERE entry=6545;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Take my update to Kadrak. Swiftly, $N.' WHERE entry=6546;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Let Kadrak know of the success we have had here holding off the night elves. Our plans are going well.' WHERE entry=6547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='$N, I thank you... but I will never forget what the Grimtotem have done to my village.' WHERE entry=6548;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Kelris has eluded the Argent Dawn for some time.$B$BFor some time they considered him dead or missing.$B$BBy ending his reign you have spared the lives of many innocent people, $N.$B$BEarthmother be praised! To sacrifice another to a servant of an Old God for personal gain is beyond disgusting!$B$BYou have done a great thing this day. Kelris was a creature of evil and sought to bring the world back to a time of chaos by worshipping such creatures as the Old Gods. Thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=6561;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Tsunaman sent you? Excellent. Then we have matters to discuss.' WHERE entry=6562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N. These are the crystals I spoke of. Intriguings...$B$BI can feel the power within them. The spirits of water cling to them. Whatever the naga were going to use these for... well, let us be glad they are no longer in their hands.' WHERE entry=6563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is interesting indeed. I am glad you have brought it to my attention.$B$BNow we have a name for our troubles... Lorgus Jett.' WHERE entry=6564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Very good!! Thank you, $N. We may not have stopped the Twilight\'s Hammer completely, but at least you have staved off another of their plans to return the Old Gods to power.$B$BWho knows what other plans they have manifesting, but we can rest easy for now.' WHERE entry=6565;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Are you prepared to take on this task?' WHERE entry=6566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Patience, $N. Pay attention!' WHERE entry=6566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There is but one way into the dragon\'s lair, $R.$B$BYou see, only the strongest of the Black Dragonflight are allowed entry into the lair of the brood mother. Many trials must be passed and the key to enter ceremoniously enchanted by General Drakkisath himself!$B$BSince you are not of black dragonkin, you may have some difficulty in obtaining passage.$B$B<Rexxar grins.>' WHERE entry=6567;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Myranda holds the note, pauses, then smiles.>$B$BHow is he? Rexxar, I mean. Oh, come now, do not look so confused. The letter was left intentionally blank. It carried with it the intentions and thoughts of its creator. Judging from its contents, it is no wonder Rexxar left it as such. Imagine if you were captured or slain and this information discovered!$B$BOh, nevermind! Myranda will help you, $R. I owe the Warchief a favor or two.$B$B<Myranda smiles.>' WHERE entry=6568;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Let Myranda have a look, $R.$B$BOh yes, these will do nicely.$B$BWith these reagents, Myranda will create for you a medallion that will grant an illusion capable of fooling the black dragonflight\'s gatekeeper.' WHERE entry=6569;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Have we run so low on able soldiers that Nefarian is sending me whelps? You will never pass my tests, broodling.' WHERE entry=6570;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent, $N. You\'ve saved me a lot of work!$B$BBut don\'t think that I\'m not grateful!' WHERE entry=6571;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is perfect -- just the thing! Well, here\'s the shipment.' WHERE entry=6581;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='One of ssseveral complete...' WHERE entry=6582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Another complete...' WHERE entry=6583;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The most hated remainsss...' WHERE entry=6584;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I had doubted your dedication, whelp. You persisted, dominating our enemies, bringing honor to our flight.$B$BI must now prepare the skulls for your ascension.' WHERE entry=6585;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Ascension...',offerrewardtext_loc2='It is merely dragon-talk, $N - more hot air than actual substantive information. Pompous, aggressive behavior is to be expected from their kind.' WHERE entry=6601;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A victory that will be remembered for many years, $N. The Drakefire Amulet will open Onyxia\'s lair. Gather your allies and bring victory to the Horde.' WHERE entry=6602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well, hi there! So Meggi told you of the trouble I have found here?' WHERE entry=6603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Aye, what can I do for you?' WHERE entry=6604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, $C. I see that there is hope yet. Are you here to assist me?' WHERE entry=6605;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, so Harlo be sendin\' you? Well, den, who might you be? I s\'pose you be wantin\' my help?' WHERE entry=6606;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Now that\'s a fine catch!$B$BCome over here, lemme show you how to set a few lines.' WHERE entry=6607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='\'Course, you must be a friend of Lumak\'s.$B$BFishin\'? I can tell you all \'bout fishin\'.' WHERE entry=6608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I\'ve always got room on my island for visitors... I reckon...' WHERE entry=6609;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You are in for a special treat, $N. Watch and learn!$B$B<Dirge begins to prepare clamlette surprise.>' WHERE entry=6610;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Dirge spits out some leather sandal bits.>$B$BPfftooey...$B$B<Dirge hacks loudly.>$B$BWhat? I\'ll have you know that leather is surprisingly high in protein and low in carbohydrates.' WHERE entry=6611;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Dirge spits out leather.>$B$BPfftey...$B$B<Dirge hacks loudly.>$B$BWhat? I\'ll have you know that leather is surprisingly high in protein and low in carbohydrates, $R.' WHERE entry=6612;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Good work, $N. Issuing that challenge to the Foulwealds and defeating their leader sends them a strong message:$B$BThe Horde is not to be trifled with.$B$BI don\'t believe that tribe will giving us much trouble for a long time.' WHERE entry=6621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Triage',offerrewardtext_loc2='Doctor $N, welcome to Horde Trauma.' WHERE entry=6622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Miraculous work, doctor. Simply miraculous.' WHERE entry=6622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful. Put on your scrubs, we are to start at once!' WHERE entry=6623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Triage',offerrewardtext_loc2='Doctor $N, welcome to Alliance Trauma.' WHERE entry=6624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Miraculous work, doctor. Simply miraculous.' WHERE entry=6624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful. Put on your scrubs, we are to start at once!' WHERE entry=6625;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thank you, $N! The work you\'ve done will be a great help, I\'m sure.$B$BI will continue my study of this diplomat and the rest of the quilboar here. If you seek greater adventure, I\'d find a few friends and head into the cave that looks like a great boar maw just over there. I\'m sure once you\'re inside you\'ll find greater challenges to face.' WHERE entry=6626;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $C. You have studied the text I asked you to, and now you have passed another of our tests.' WHERE entry=6627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Life is full of questions, $C. You will never be able to answer all of them, but with some time and study, perhaps you will become a little more knowledgeable.' WHERE entry=6627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N. I had my doubts if you studied the text I asked you to get, but you\'ve answered correctly.' WHERE entry=6628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='There is only one rule I feel you must know if you wish to survive in this world: the more you know, the more you\'ll see.$B$BIf you study, if you observe, then you will begin to see things in the world that no other $R will see.' WHERE entry=6628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Grundig Darkcloud is dead! $N, I will always be grateful for what you\'ve done here today.' WHERE entry=6629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I have witnessed many naga attacks since I arrived here. It puts my mind at ease that Vorsha will no longer roam freely.$B$BWe are in your debt, $N.' WHERE entry=6641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.' WHERE entry=6642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.' WHERE entry=6643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.' WHERE entry=6644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.' WHERE entry=6645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.' WHERE entry=6646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These\'ll werk nicely, matey. Me brother needs em still tickin\' and kickin,\' else they go sour... Ye don\'t want to taste no sour rat kabob.' WHERE entry=6661;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Poor Monty. Ever since the Gnomeregan incident, he hasn\'t been the same. That boy has never seen an ocean in his life, let alone being some kind of pirate.$B$B<Nipsy sighs.>$B$BAt least he keeps the flow of twitching critters coming.' WHERE entry=6662;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Most excellent, young thief.$B$BYou look a bit beaten down, but no worse for the wear.$B$BA long journey awaits you - long and rewarding. Are you prepared to finally embrace your destiny among the masters of Ravenholdt?$B$BSpeak with the guards outside. They will get you started.' WHERE entry=6681;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hey, nice work! Keep this up and the other rogues might stop spitting on you.' WHERE entry=6701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Yes, it is time, $C.' WHERE entry=6721;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thanks again, $N. You do the Horde proud...' WHERE entry=6741;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Yes $C, thank you for coming. I apologize about the misunderstanding... the air is thick with mistrust between the Arch Druid here and Keeper Remulos in Moonglade. Each suspect the other of chicanery, and the fact that strange corruptions of Teldrassil continue unabated are still an issue here. It does little to quell mistrust.$B$BRegardless, our duty to the Cenarion Circle remains... even if those who lead it may disagree with one another.' WHERE entry=6761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Rabine Saturna',offerrewardtext_loc2='I am Rabine Saturna, and on behalf of Keeper Remulos and all of the denizens of this sacred glade I bid you welcome.$B$BI appreciate your interest and eagerness to assist the Cenarion Circle. I also know that Arch Druid of Darnassus expressed his displeasure to you in your lending us aid. Rest assured that it is for the greater good, and that you will be safe from any ill-conceived repercussions you may be the target of.$B$BYou are among friends here, $N.' WHERE entry=6762;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These are some good pieces, $N. I can use them to fashion new equipment for our troops.$B$BIf my supply level gets high enough, then maybe our seasoned fighting units will enter the field!' WHERE entry=6781;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The blood of our enemies has been shed. I shall mix this blood with the rest that has been gathered. Once the offering is complete, the Ice Lord shall show these Stormpike dogs the full wrath of the Frostwolf Clan!' WHERE entry=6801;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done well, $C. The corrupted elementals you cured were an outrage to all bodies of water. Our strength lies in our purity and if we are to win our war with the others, we must remain strong.' WHERE entry=6804;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your bravery is proven, as is your worth to us.  Perhaps I may have future tasks for you, tasks more befitting a valued ally of the Waterlords.' WHERE entry=6805;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, so you do have the strength.  And you have the cunning as well, for Blackrock Spire is more than a match for brute strength alone.$B$BIndeed $N, you may yet prove a valued ally to us...' WHERE entry=6821;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done what most of your kind would think impossible.  You have faced the beings of the Molten Core, and triumphed!$B$BFor so small a creature, you have displayed great resource.$B$BSome day, perhaps we might strike a true allegiance between your kind and the Waterlords.' WHERE entry=6822;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your exploits against our enemies ring through the chambers of the Waterlords, $N.  It was thought by some that your form is too small and fragile to fight in our war, but you have made great gains.  You have earned respect among us, an unbelievable feat.' WHERE entry=6823;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have the hands!  You defeated the fire captains!  I would not have thought it possible, had I not known you and what you are capable of.$B$B$N, your exploits are without number, but word of this last feat will send waves among the Waterlords.  Your name may one day be legend to us.$B$BSpeak with me again, $N.  I may have yet another task...' WHERE entry=6824;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The fleet feeds on their flesh. It consumes the enemy.$B$BFlight is imminent!' WHERE entry=6825;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='More! More! Bring more for they are soon to be ready!' WHERE entry=6826;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Not enough! I would expect this level of work from an initiate, but you, $N? Come on, soldier! HUSTLE! More flesh is needed!' WHERE entry=6827;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='x',objectives_loc2='x' WHERE entry=6841;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='x',objectives_loc2='x' WHERE entry=6842;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well great monkey toads! What have you got here? It\'s sort of book shaped, I guess... I\'ll try crack this shell on it.$B$BLayo sent you to me from Silithus? I\'ve only heard very hushed rumblings - which I guess aren\'t all that hushed when you think about it - about the horrors that are going on out there. Couple that with my lack of pleasure for anything bug-like, and you\'ve got the recipe for me needing to stay here with the books!' WHERE entry=6844;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, $N - I had hoped you would stop by. I am glad to see you well.$B$BI received notice you would be coming in from the field, and I wanted to personally express the Cenarion Circle\'s gratitude for the assistance you\'ve given us thus far. No doubt there are more secrets to uncover from Silithus; your delivery to Umber should prove most interesting once uncovered. Please, accept this as a token of our continued appreciation for your aid.$B$BThank you, generous $C.' WHERE entry=6845;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, the orders! They say I\'m to assault at will, and my will says... now!' WHERE entry=6846;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N. I will use the power of this charm to augment the magic that has already been gathered. When enough power has been amassed, I shall focus the collected energies and call upon the Forest Lord to aid our cause.' WHERE entry=6881;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It\'s about time! Now we can show the Alliance their folly in coming to Alterac Valley!' WHERE entry=6901;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is exactly what I need! A fathom core is an incredible well of information that we will be able to draw much good from. Whatever the Twilight\'s Hammer is up to in there - and believe me when I say it is no good - my comrades and I will now uncover.$B$BYou\'ve done well here today; the Earthen Ring looks upon you warmly for assisting us. You\'ve also helped the Horde as a whole, and for that you should be proud.' WHERE entry=6921;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Baron Aquanis',offerrewardtext_loc2='This... this is quite the find, $N.$B$BYou acquired this from Baron Aquanis in Blackfathom, you say?  Baron Aquanis has long been thought of as a corrupted elemental power; this globe will prove what exactly had corrupted him.  While it would be no surprise if it turned out to be the Twilight\'s Hammer, our studies will also show how they did it as well.$B$BYou did well in bringing this to me.  Please - take this, along with the Earthen Ring\'s warmest regards.' WHERE entry=6922;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The flight will be ready soon. Continue your efforts!' WHERE entry=6941;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Keep em coming, soldier! The Aerie gryphons will be ready to strike in no time at all!' WHERE entry=6942;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Can you see it? Look at them, soldier! They\'re coming around... Soon, Ichman\'s flight will once again strike at the heart of the valley! Stormpike will rule the skies!' WHERE entry=6943;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello.  I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... "Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil.  Huzzah.' WHERE entry=6961;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You\'re quite the helper to ol\' Great-father Winter there, $N.  Have a great Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BHere\'s a little something... you know, for the effort.' WHERE entry=6962;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Y-y-you can h-h-hear me!  Thank the b-b-bottom line!$B$BI\'m not really a s-s-snowman - my n-n-name is Sacks, and I w-w-work for the Orgrimmar b-b-branch of Smokywood Pastures... I g-g-got sent out here to look for a m-m-missing package, when I was attacked by a c-c-creature I have never seen b-b-before!$B$BSo v-v-very cold...' WHERE entry=6963;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The Feast of Winter Veil, you say?  Alas, in times past it held a more substantial meaning to us tauren.  Nowadays, it seems as though others have turned the legend of this season of renewal into something that helps to sell candies and presents.$B$BIt\'s no surprise that Furmund is bitter about that sort of change.  He and other tauren like him cling to our past like a banner of war.  While I think a little celebration is always good, it is important to remember the origins of the Feast.' WHERE entry=6964;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh... I have never seen anything like this...' WHERE entry=6981;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Hello, $R. What can I do for you?' WHERE entry=6981;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, you got them. Good work, $N! These supplies are a little musty from sitting in that dark mine for so long, but we\'ll make use of them nonetheless.$B$BThank you, $N. Your deeds are vital to the maintenance of our fighting forces.' WHERE entry=6982;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You found it!  You\'ve saved Smokywood Pasture\'s Feast of Winter Veil!$B$BPoor Sacks... we\'ll be sure to send a team out there and figure out a way to unfreeze him.  Hopefully, he\'ll be back in time for the day of the Feast; he\'ll need to make up missed time working though.  Still, this wouldn\'t even be possible if it weren\'t for you!' WHERE entry=6983;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello, adventurer!$B$BThe goblins told me that you have earned a special gift this holiday season, and I am pleased to give it to you.  Here you go - have a wondrous Feast of Winter Veil this and every season in the future.' WHERE entry=6984;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You got them! Nicely done, $N! And I hope you saw a few dwarves during your raid, and shed their blood for the Frostwolves!' WHERE entry=6985;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I can only hope that those charged with collecting ram hides are as determined as you, $N.$B$BAt this rate, we will have the stables full in a matter of hours!' WHERE entry=7001;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Without your help, the Frostwolf Wolf Riders would not have mounts to ride into battle. You do us a great service!' WHERE entry=7001;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='While some of our soldiers are busy capturing wolves for the stable master, others must provide for the simple necessities that riding requires. I am speaking of riding harnesses, of course.$B$BYou must strike at the indigenous rams of the region. The very same rams that the Stormpike cavalry uses as mounts!$B$BSlay them and return to me with their hides. Once we have gathered enough hides, we will fashion harnesses for the riders. The Frostwolf Wolf Riders will ride once more!',offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, soldier. I will notify you when I have stockpiled enough of the hides.$B$BCarry on!' WHERE entry=7002;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Splendifimous!  Not only am I glad to see that you\'ve returned with the residue, but also with all your major appendages intact!  That is, well, there was never any danger in using the Ultra-Shrinker, now was there!$B$BI do appreciate your effort on my behalf, $N.  Truly, you are a friend to goblins everywhere.  Accept this as a token of my appreciation!' WHERE entry=7003;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello.  I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... "Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil.  Huzzah.' WHERE entry=7021;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello.  I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... "Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil.  Huzzah.' WHERE entry=7022;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello.  I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... "Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil.  Huzzah.' WHERE entry=7023;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello.  I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... "Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil.  Huzzah.' WHERE entry=7024;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You\'re quite the helper to ol\' Greatfather Winter there, $N.  Have a great Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BHere\'s a little something... you know, for the effort.' WHERE entry=7025;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='The Stormpike Brigade cannot charge into battle bareback! We require harnesses for our mounts, after all, we are not savages.$B$BWhile we could easily slay the rams that roam near our base for the leather required to fashion a harness, doing so would be idiotic. We need those rams for mounts.$B$BYou must strike at our enemy\'s base, slaying the frostwolves they use as mounts and taking their hides. Return their hides to me so that harnesses may be made for the cavalry. Go!',offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, soldier. I will notify you when I have stockpiled enough of the hides.$B$BCarry on!' WHERE entry=7026;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The stables will be full in no time at all. Keep up the good work!' WHERE entry=7027;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Without your help, the Stormpike Ram Riders would not have mounts to ride into battle. You do us a great service!' WHERE entry=7027;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ha ha ha! I knew you\'d be back.$B$B<Willow mutters>$B$B...So easy to convince.$B$B...Will do anything for the right price. Heh heh heh...' WHERE entry=7028;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thank you for returning this, $N. With the remaining liquid you brought me, I can continue my studies.$B$BWhile there is still much to do, you have helped to heal some of the corruption that Vyletongue spread through Maraudon. Please take this with my gratitude.' WHERE entry=7029;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Thank you for returning this, $N. With the remaining liquid you brought me, I can continue my studies.$B$BWhile there is still much to do, you have helped to heal some of the corruption that Vyletongue spread through Maraudon. Please take this with my gratitude.' WHERE entry=7041;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Y-y-you can h-h-hear me! Thank the b-b-bottom line!$B$BI\'m not really a s-s-snowman - my n-n-name is Sacks, and I w-w-work for the Ironforge b-b-branch of Smokywood Pastures... I g-g-got sent out here to look for a m-m-missing package, when I was attacked by a c-c-creature I have never seen b-b-before!$B$BSo v-v-very cold...' WHERE entry=7042;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You found it!  You\'ve saved Smokywood Pasture\'s Feast of Winter Veil!$B$BPoor Sacks... we\'ll be sure to send a team out there and figure out a way to unfreeze him.  Hopefully, he\'ll be back in time for the day of the Feast; he\'ll need to make up missed time working though.  Still, this wouldn\'t even be possible if it weren\'t for you!' WHERE entry=7043;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Now that you have recovered the two parts of my scepter, I have hope that Maraudon may one day be rid of the Vyle corruption.' WHERE entry=7044;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ho ho hello, adventurer!$B$BThe goblins told me that you have earned a special gift this holiday season, and I am pleased to give it to you.  Here you go - have a wondrous Feast of Winter Veil this and every season in the future.' WHERE entry=7045;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Please take this, and know that the power allotted to you now must be used for good. Continue your journey through the caverns, and with hope, you will find the remains of my uncle. Much danger awaits you, $N.$B$BSpeak with me again should the need arise.' WHERE entry=7046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='If you wish to restart the ritual, please abandon our first attempt and then speak to me again.' WHERE entry=7046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The legends and lore surrounding the Winter Veil are ones that have faded from the forefront of public thought over the years.  Yes, I know that the goblins are helping to revive the season for their own ends, the fact that our people reflect upon it at least in some form does good to keep such lore alive.$B$BYour desire to go beyond the material and learn about our past is an admirable trait, young $C.  I salute your wisdom.' WHERE entry=7061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The Feast of Winter Veil, you say? Alas, in times past it held a more substantial meaning to us dwarves. Nowadays, it seems as though others have turned the legend of Greatfather Winter into something that helps to sell candies and presents.$B$BIt\'s no surprise that Goli is bitter about that sort of change. He and other dwarves like him cling to our past like a banner of war. While I think a little celebration is always good, it is important to remember the origins of the Feast.' WHERE entry=7062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The legends and lore surrounding the Winter Veil are ones that have faded from the forefront of public thought over the years. While I recognize that the goblins are helping to revive the season for their own ends, the fact that the citizenry thinks about it at least in some form does good to keep such lore alive.$B$BYour desire to go beyond the material and learn about our past is an admirable trait, young $C. I salute your erudite nature.' WHERE entry=7063;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is most wonderful news, $N! Thank you!$B$BI will speak with Marandis and ask his wisdom on the topic of Zaetar\'s remains, but at least you have overcome the hardest of the tasks.$B$BI was told that if we were successful in our mission, I had permission to reward those who aided us. I was given these items as tokens from our people--you may choose one.' WHERE entry=7064;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is most wonderful news, $N! Thank you!$B$BAlthough it concerns me that you were not able to bring back Zaetar\'s remains, who am I to question the will of Cenarius\' first born. Perhaps now the will of the centaur will break and their thirst for blood will lesson--we can only hope.$B$BIf successful in our mission, I was given these items to reward any who aided us. You may choose one as a token of thanks.' WHERE entry=7065;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='So my brother has finally found peace? I am proud to have lived to see this day. In all his arrogance and anger, I truly thought he was lost to us, but this... this symbol of his sacrifice only proves that he is not lost--he has only been reborn. He takes his place in nature as was his duty.$B$BThank you, $N. By bringing this to me, you have secured a small amount of hope that I thought I had once lost. This seed will be important to the people of this war-torn land some day... I can sense it.' WHERE entry=7066;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is it, $R! This is it! Now I can begin the great task of uniting the tribes. Thank you.$B$BTake this for your efforts, please. I hope when next we meet, it will be on much different terms.' WHERE entry=7067;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, these be perfect for me magics. Here, you take one of these trinkets and be on your way... me got much studyin\' to do.' WHERE entry=7068;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These are perfect, $N. I actually had other adventurers return from there also and from them I was able to fashion these... please, feel free to take one for your hard work. And thank you again for more samples to study.' WHERE entry=7070;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done! Graveyards are vital to our control of Alterac Valley. When you capture one, you help ensure the Alliance\'s sovereignty here.$B$BGo now, $N. Reenter the battle, and if you see a graveyard under the Horde\'s control... you know what to do!' WHERE entry=7081;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N! With each graveyard under our control, the spirits of our enemies will wander more lost and aimless.' WHERE entry=7082;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I heard of your mission\'s success! That pleases me...$B$BOur troops can now charge forward with impunity, and show the Alliance that Alterac Valley is no place for them!' WHERE entry=7101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I received a field report stating you helped secure an enemy banner. Well done, $N! With their ranged troops out of position we can move the line of battle forward!' WHERE entry=7102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It\'s good to see fresh troops here, $N, but with a little luck you\'ll get into some action and won\'t be fresh for long!$B$BSpeak with me again. I have tasks I must discuss with you....' WHERE entry=7121;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You did it! Well done, $N!$B$BWhen we control a mine and have troops stationed there, it\'s much easier to gather minerals and supplies from it.' WHERE entry=7122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hail, $N! It is good to see a $C like yourself, eager to do his part for the Horde. Speak with me again, for I have vital tasks for you...' WHERE entry=7123;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You captured a mine! With our own warriors protecting it, it will be much simpler to extract minerals from its depths, or gather supplies that have been cached there.$B$BWell done, $N>. The deed you have done is a great boon to our battle efforts.' WHERE entry=7124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N!  With the Horde\'s nose bloodied after the death of their general, we\'ll have the breathing room we need to explore!' WHERE entry=7141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Go, $N.  Go to Alterac Valley and defeat the orc general!' WHERE entry=7141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N!  Stormpikes have no hope in this foolish invasion.$B$BHah!  So far, all they\'ve done is get their general killed!' WHERE entry=7142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='That burning sensation you feel is your soul being awakened. Your spirit has accepted the call to arms.$B$BYou are now one of the Frostwolf, $N. Congratulations.$B$BCarry this insignia with you at all times. As you advance among the ranks of Frostwolf, I will replace the insignia with other, more powerful insignias.$B$BPerhaps someday you will be exalted among the Frostwolf Clan. Should that day ever come, you will be granted the Eye of Command.' WHERE entry=7161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Take and wear this insignia with pride, $N. As your rank among the Stormpike grows, so too will the insignia. Return to me as you gain honor with Stormpike, and I shall replace your insignia with other, more powerful insignias.$B$BPerhaps someday you will grow to be a legend on this field of battle. Should that day ever come, you will be granted the Eye of Command.' WHERE entry=7162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='<Warmaster Laggrond salutes you.>$B$BIt is your time, $N. You have done much for the Frostwolf Clan and in doing so, earned a place as not only a soldier of Frostwolf but also as a friend.$B$BWell done! Present your initiate\'s insignia.$B',offerrewardtext_loc2='This new insignia reflects your rank amongst the Frostwolf. Keep it on you at all times.$B$BAnd mage... Die with honor!' WHERE entry=7163;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='It is good to see you again, $C. I had not expected you to return. Alas, you have proven yourself a brave and honorable soldier of the Frostwolf.$B$BYour time has come again, $N. You have earned a new ranking and as such, a new insignia denoting this rise in stature.$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='<Warmaster Laggrond salutes.>$B$BGo, $N! Continue your defense of the Frostwolf. This war must be won! For Drek\'Thar! For the Warchief!' WHERE entry=7164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='I must know, $N. When you look directly into the eyes of the enemy, do you see fear? Do they now cower in your presence? They must realize that they are defeated!$B$BYou have earned reverence among the Guard.$B$BPresent your insignia!',offerrewardtext_loc2='When we first met, I would have never guessed that a hero was in the making. Carry on, soldier!' WHERE entry=7165;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='Your radiate command and power, shaman. Exalted in the eyes of Frostwolf - the enemy cowers at the mention of your name.$B$BRise, Hero of Frostwolf. Rise and be honored!$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='Soon, all on the field of battle will be under your watchful eye. Command of the Valley and its troops will be yours!' WHERE entry=7166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='Drek\'Thar sings your praises. Kalimdor is abuzz with tales of your heroics. The Warchief glows - your stalwart defense of our clan has pleased him greatly.$B$BYou have earned the Eye of Command.$B$BPresent your insignia, Commander $N.$B$B<Warmaster Laggrond salutes>',offerrewardtext_loc2='Channel the power of the insignia. Let the enemy hear your words. The might of the Horde is unquestionable!' WHERE entry=7167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='Most do not live long enough to rise above their own mediocrity. You have proven yourself to be an exemplary soldier, $C. The time has come.$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='Let our enemies see that a soldier of rank has struck them down! Fight for the glory of Stormpike!' WHERE entry=7168;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='The base buzzes with news of your exploits in the Field of Strife! You have struck mighty blows against our enemy - crushing their morale! For this, you have earned a rank of honor among the Stormpike.$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='The king has been made aware of your battlefront heroics, $C. Continue in your stalwart defense of the Stormpike Guard!' WHERE entry=7169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='I must know, $N. When you look directly into the eyes of the enemy, do you see fear? Do they now cower in your presence? They must realize that they are defeated!$B$BYou have earned reverence among the Guard.$B$BPresent your insignia!',offerrewardtext_loc2='When we first met, I would have never guessed that a hero was in the making. Carry on, soldier!' WHERE entry=7170;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='Your radiate command and power, shaman. Exalted in the eyes of Frostwolf - the enemy cowers at the mention of your name.$B$BRise, Hero of Frostwolf. Rise and be honored!$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='Soon, all on the field of battle will be under your watchful eye. Command of the Valley and its troops will be yours!' WHERE entry=7171;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='It is good to see you again, $C. I had not expected you to return. Alas, you have proven yourself a brave and honorable soldier of the Frostwolf.$B$BYour time has come again, $N. You have earned a new ranking and as such, a new insignia denoting this rise in stature.$B$BPresent your insignia.',offerrewardtext_loc2='<Warmaster Laggrond salutes.>$B$BGo, $N! Continue your defense of the Frostwolf. This war must be won! For Drek\'Thar! For the Warchief!' WHERE entry=7172;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! I will have these sent by courier to the Undercity at once!$B$BAs for you - here is payment, as promised. Keep the change, you filthy beast!' WHERE entry=7201;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These are some good pieces, $N. I can use them to fashion new equipment for our troops.$B$BIf my supply level gets high enough, then maybe our seasoned fighting units will enter the field!' WHERE entry=7223;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These will do nicely. I\'ll melt them down and patch them up and you\'ll never know they came from those Stormpike cowards!$B$BThanks, $N. And let me polish up that armor of yours...' WHERE entry=7224;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='To become a soldier of Frostwolf, one must first be tested...' WHERE entry=7241;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your heroics will not go unnoticed, $N.$B$BI must waste no time if he is to be saved. Sylvanas must be contacted!' WHERE entry=7281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You did remember to burn the corpse, didn\'t you?' WHERE entry=7282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Unbelievable! You did free them, right? Right??? Well at the very least we know where they were held.' WHERE entry=7301;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done! The information you recovered will be invaluable to our cause.' WHERE entry=7302;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='My soothing turtle bisque will keep you warm on a cold night... if you care about that kind of thing.' WHERE entry=7321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent! I am a Tauren of my word, $R. The arrows are yours.' WHERE entry=7341;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A done deal if I ever saw one! The arrows are yours.' WHERE entry=7342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='$N, it is but one of thousands. A job well done nonetheless.' WHERE entry=7361;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Aye, this is definitely gnome. Well done, $R, but there is more work to be done.' WHERE entry=7362;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It would be easier if they just accepted their illness and gave in to your healing touch. It would also probably be less fun. Carry on! We\'ll cure them, one way or another.' WHERE entry=7363;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Praise be to Benedictus! Another lost soul, soon to be saved by the white hot flames of the Light!$B$BGo ye, oh soldier of Light! More must be saved!' WHERE entry=7366;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='To be in the presence of the Oracle Tree... it is almost to feel wisdom take form. Let me continue the telling...$B$BWith Teldrassil grown, the Arch Druid approached the dragons for their blessings, as the dragons had placed upon Nordrassil in ancient times. But Nozdormu, Lord of Time, refused to give his blessing, chiding the druid for his arrogance. In agreement with Nozdormu, Alexstrasza also refused Staghelm, and without her blessing, Teldrassil\'s growth has been flawed and unpredictable...' WHERE entry=7383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='<nyi> <txt> The Scale Crafters' WHERE entry=7384;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='You have the option of offering larger quantities of the blood taken from our enemies. I will be glad to accept gallon sized offerings, $N.',offerrewardtext_loc2='The blood of our enemies has been shed. I shall mix this blood with the rest that has been gathered. Once the offering is complete, the Ice Lord shall show these Stormpike dogs the full wrath of the Frostwolf Clan!' WHERE entry=7385;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='There are times which you may be entrenched in battle for days or weeks on end. During those longer periods of activity you may end up collecting large clusters of the Frostwolf\'s storm crystals.$B$BThe Circle accepts such offerings, $N.',offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N. I will use the power of these charms to augment the magic that has already been gathered. When enough power has been amassed, I shall focus the collected energies and call upon the Forest Lord to aid our cause.' WHERE entry=7386;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You now have license to decimate dwarves by the dozen, $C!$B$B<Yazra stares off into the distance for a moment.>$B$BYou never forget your first de-spining...' WHERE entry=7401;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh, thank you for freeing me! You - ranked number one. Everyone else - ranked number two or lower.$B$BI knew my life was destined for more than just being an appetizer to some ogre!' WHERE entry=7429;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have found it! A curse upon that miserable imp. Alas, my material possessions are meager at best. You may choose from what I have to offer.' WHERE entry=7441;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='We thank you, hero.' WHERE entry=7461;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You open the chest to find...' WHERE entry=7462;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! Who are you again? Oh it matters not. What was I supposed to give you? Hrm... well you are a $C, perhaps you will find this useful.' WHERE entry=7463;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A shame... a tragedy. The items are lost you say? No trace of him, eh?' WHERE entry=7481;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='My associate, the night elf scholar, Runethorn, is recruiting her allies for this task.' WHERE entry=7481;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A shame... a tragedy. The items are lost you say? No trace of him, eh?' WHERE entry=7482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='My associate, the night elf scholar, Runethorn, is recruiting her allies for this task.' WHERE entry=7482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Lydros yawns.>$B$BAs promised, the Arcanum of Rapidity. Don\'t spend it all in once place.$B$B<Lydros snickers.>' WHERE entry=7483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Don\'t hurt yourself when applying the enchantment, $R.' WHERE entry=7484;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Yes, yes... Calm yourself. As promised, here is your Arcanum.' WHERE entry=7485;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hydraxis\' voice descends from the waters\' surface...$B$B"Choose that which best suits you, $N.  May it protect you against the foes of the Waterlords."' WHERE entry=7486;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I am now able to transport you to the Molten Core. Ask and it shall be done.' WHERE entry=7487;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You retrieved the web!  Well done, $N!  Lethtendris, like many elves of her ilk, are blind to the dangers the abuse of magic can cause to our world.  They believe they are masters of magic; they do not realize that they are slaves to their own addiction.  Her death saddens me, but it was necessary.$B$BThank you, $N.  I will have the energies within the web released safely over a wide area, and then I\'ll destroy it to prevent future magical exploits.' WHERE entry=7488;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done well, $N. This web holds within it vast stores of the magic of Dire Maul, and I fear what damage may be unleashed if those energies were harnessed by one so irresponsible as Lethtendris. I am saddened by her death, but I know that she could never part with her web while alive.$B$BThank you, $N. I will send the web to students of magic more responsible than Lethtendris. They will be the new wardens of its power.' WHERE entry=7489;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is a great victory for the Horde, $N. So many times you have honored your Warchief. It is time for the Warchief to honor you.' WHERE entry=7490;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Choose your reward and let the celebration of your glorious victory begin.' WHERE entry=7491;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, it is good to see a $C heed my summons. I have need of your services, $N, and fear they will take you down a dangerous path...$B$BA path into Dire Maul.' WHERE entry=7492;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hail, $N.  I am pleased to see you, but regret that our meeting is not under more pleasant conditions.$B$BListen close, for I have a vital task for you...' WHERE entry=7494;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='For so many years I was held under her captivating gaze. Finally, to see justice meted and the honor of Stormwind restored! Today, we celebrate this glorious victory!' WHERE entry=7495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Few are graced with such ceremony, $N. Please, choose your reward so that we may begin the celebration.' WHERE entry=7496;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7498;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7499;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7500;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7502;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7505;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.' WHERE entry=7506;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You could have gotten quite a lot of gold for this book on the black market, $N. Especially since the protective seal has been broken, leaving the secrets of dragon slaying viewable to any with the requisite intellect to consume the knowledge held within the sacred pages.$B$BPerhaps a grand reward is in order... Well, a reward that will require enormous effort to obtain.$B$B<Lydros grins.>' WHERE entry=7507;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='If you manage to enter the lair of the dragon, heat the blade under her fiery breath, and ultimately temper it in her blood, I shall bind the blade for your use.' WHERE entry=7508;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Lydros murmurs something unintelligible.>$B$BAs promised, $C, the blade of Quel\'Serrar.' WHERE entry=7509;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It will take time for our scholars to study the pendant you brought us.  But for your service to the Horde I would like to offer you a small token.$B$BThank you, $N.  Your acts bring honor to you, and to us.' WHERE entry=7541;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Greetings, $N, and welcome.  Are you here to study near the Altar of Storms as I am, perhaps to harness its energy for some hidden purpose...$B$BOr... are you here to speak with me?  Yes, I believe you are.$B$BYou want to master a dreadsteed?  Such is no easy task.  It will cost you no small amounts of blood, sweat... and of course gold.  But a dreadsteed of Xoroth is a prize well worth winning so if interested, listen on...' WHERE entry=7562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, very good. I will have this blood distilled into an ink and use it for the parchment I promised you. And perhaps I will save just a little for myself, as I hear its taste is quite euphoric...' WHERE entry=7563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh, it\'s blood. It must be from master Mor\'zul then. He is so enamored with the stuff, and loves to see it spilled. I, however, prefer it coursing through the veins of a small rodent. It stays warm that way... until you want it.$B$BThis is powerful blood. Mor\'zul must be making another parchment to summon a dreadsteed! How exciting!$B$BIf that\'s true, and you\'re going to perform the ritual, then... you\'re going to need a lot more than blood, my friend.' WHERE entry=7564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, a most excellent recovery. The blood will suppress the Doomguard\'s magical defenses.' WHERE entry=7581;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I merely need to combine the blood of the Wildspawn with these crystals and the prison shall be ready for use.' WHERE entry=7582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have done as I have asked. You are ready to be given the knowledge to conjure and control the beast.' WHERE entry=7583;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh boy, here we go again.' WHERE entry=7601;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Give me a minute and I\'ll combine the essences into Fel fire.' WHERE entry=7602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A deal is a deal! Quickly, take this and write this down. I don\'t have time! My greatest conjuration is upon us!' WHERE entry=7603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='It has been a pleasure doing business with you, $N!$B$BOn behalf of TB Ltd., I wish you luck in your search for Sulfuras!' WHERE entry=7604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='$C, you are about to undergo a rigorous series of events which shall test all of your abilities.$B$BI suggest that you listen to the story that I have to tell.$B$BBe warned, you must complete this task alone. It is recommended that your allies remain at a distance. Interference by outside agents will result in a most severe punishment.$B$BDestiny has led you and you alone here. Battle with honor. Harness the Light.' WHERE entry=7621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your tenacity and courage are astounding, $Gpriest:priestess;. You have earned the right to hold the Splinter of Nordrassil. Only one task remains: The Eye of Shadow must be recovered. Scour the world.' WHERE entry=7622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='My patience spans the millenia, $C.  But do not think that allows you more than an instant of my time...' WHERE entry=7623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, how splendid! After rotting a week, this heart will prove a succulent treat! Perhaps I will send for Ulathek\'s head and place it before me as I eat...$B$BYou have done me a service, $C, and so my patience for you has grown. Marginally.' WHERE entry=7624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There it is! I can hardly believe you got it! You must have struck a big deal with that Dreadlord or else paid a large sum, or both!$B$BMor\'zul will have his ink very soon and then he can finally make the glyph parchment, so you can open a portal to Xoroth and pull through it one of the famed dreadsteeds!' WHERE entry=7625;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Very good! I hope these elixirs weren\'t too hard to get. Sometimes alchemists can be so miserly with their creations...$B$BI\'ll make the bell and keep it until you\'re ready for your ritual.' WHERE entry=7626;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='There they are! I hear that dark iron ore is only found in the depths of Blackrock, and I\'m sure these shards weren\'t easy to find either. I am often awed at the dedication you warlocks have. If you instead bent all that energy into the art of bug catching, oh... such a feast you would enjoy!$B$BSorry, a small digression. I\'ll create the wheel and keep it for you until you\'re ready for your ritual.' WHERE entry=7627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, very good. I\'ll need these to contain the fires of the candle. Now that I have the scales, I\'ll make the candle and hold onto it until you\'re ready to begin your ritual for the Circle of Greater Summoning.' WHERE entry=7628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, good. J\'eevee created the parchment. How was the Scholomance? Charming, don\'t you think? And the bugs there... I hear they\'re delicious!$B$BWell done, $N, and thank you for returning my jar. I\'ve had it for a long time... and it\'s not for sale!' WHERE entry=7629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You got it! Nicely done! Now I can create the lodestone. When you\'re finally ready for your ritual to create the Circle of Greater Summoning, you\'ll want a lodestone to make sure the ritual doesn\'t fizzle out!' WHERE entry=7630;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The Xorothian Dreadsteed\'s spirit is beaten.  Although rage pulses through its ghostly flanks, you know that the beast\'s soul is yours...$B$BIt whispers dark magic into your mind and instills within you the knowledge to summon a dreadsteed.' WHERE entry=7631;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Of course I recognize my own leaves. Look at that! It\'s in perfect condition.$B$BHow good of you to return it, $C.$B$BPerhaps you could be of service to us and we to you.' WHERE entry=7632;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your diligence and integrity has been noted, $C.$B$BWe are Ancients: Protectors of this once great forest. Our physical forms were destroyed 10,000 years ago when Archimonde and the Burning Legion marched upon Hyjal. Our spirits, however, remain intact.$B$BThere are tasks that we can offer. Tasks that if completed will open up the secrets of the Ancients to you.$B$BKnow this, should you complete these tasks, merely return to this rock and we shall answer the calling.' WHERE entry=7633;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='May my leaves provide your arrows protection from harm. May your arrows strike true. May the enemies of our world be smitten.' WHERE entry=7634;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A most foul dragon this one was. The sinew reeks of evil.$B$BGive me a moment to cleanse the filth from this flesh and apply the proper enchantments.' WHERE entry=7635;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have served us well, $N! Take this stave and combine it with the bow string that Stoma is able to create. Together, they form a most formidable weapon.' WHERE entry=7636;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Blessings onto you, friend $C! Your donation goes far beyond what was needed. Your sacrifice will not only help us recover what we have lost, but also help us to help those most in need here in Ironforge.$B$BNow, let me make sure I\'ve suitably prepared this censer for your future needs...' WHERE entry=7637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I am glad to see you $N.  I know that you have awaited word as to how to acquire your charger, and now that time has come.$B$BYou will be surely tested in many different ways, but most importantly in your willingness to rise above numerous obstacles thrust before you.  These are not done as a learning exercise - your stature is beyond simple educational tests.  You must save your future companion from the clutches of the evil you have spent your life fighting.$B$BTake heed, your time has come!' WHERE entry=7638;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Yes, this will do. You will be called upon more than once during this process to make acts of sacrifice; I am glad to see that you are willing to do just that. Sacrifice is a key component in what it takes to uphold the duties of being a Paladin... but I don\'t have to lecture you on that.$B$BNow $N, you will need to show due judgment in your actions. To that end, this censer will act as your vessel to dispense such judgment on tortured spirits of lands lost to us.' WHERE entry=7639;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $N. To render the judgment of the Light on those that dwell in darkness is a task we must approach with vim and zeal; you have done just that with your sacrifice in Ironforge and your judgments of the spirits in Terrordale.$B$BYour next steps will call on both sacrifice and judgment again as you now strive to reclaim the spirit of a fallen charger who now serves a Death Knight known as Darkreaver.' WHERE entry=7640;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Hello there - Lord Shadowbreaker sent me word ahead of time that you\'d be coming around this way to see me. I\'m willing to make the barding you need, but it won\'t be either cheap or easy; let\'s get that out in the open first and foremost.$B$BI will say this much, and Grayson will back me up when I make this claim... you\'ll not find better barding made anywhere in all of Azeroth than right here.' WHERE entry=7641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This... well, this is exactly what I needed.  You\'re quite the resourceful $C, aren\'t you?$B$BAll right then, let\'s get this barding finished up for you!' WHERE entry=7642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='The Ancient Equine Spirit accepts the offering of the Manna-Enriched Horse Feed, nuzzling the container as it helps itself to the special oats and grains. After it has eaten a little, it looks at the barding you possess and positions itself as though it wants you to place it upon its back...' WHERE entry=7643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You\'ve come far, my friend. Your barding is now suitably prepared for the last task at hand.$B$BYou will be using this barding to harness your charger once the task of redemption is complete. Before that, however, you will have a monumental struggle to overcome. Your time draws near - huzzah!$B$BThere is one last item that needs to be made before we begin this, $N. Hopefully your resourcefulness has not departed you since you had your barding made...' WHERE entry=7644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='YES, NOW WHO - wait - you\'re giving me the gold too? You weren\'t the one who called me mad (actually they called me a fruitcake nut-job)... still, you\'re willing to show sacrifice even for wrongs you\'ve not committed?$B$BI... I misjudged you, $N.  Should you need more horse feed, come see me. I will give it to you free of charge. Thank you... noble $C.$B$BI am going to keep the money though - I\'m not that much of a nut-job as to give up a fortune.' WHERE entry=7645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='These are fine specimens, $N - the final pieces are now in place. At long last, your time has come!$B$BIn the depths of the Great Ossuary of Scholomance are the skeletal remains of many beings. Amongst them is a once-noble charger. The hollowed soul of this charger now serves as the steed for Death Knight Darkreaver. It is he whom you will face, and it is this steed that you will pass judgment upon. Only you, $N, can redeem its soul and save it from the torment of its servitude.' WHERE entry=7646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A glimmer of life - long vacant from the poor beast - shines in its eyes as you hand its judged soul back to it. You feel a holy rush of power surge around you as you place the barding on its back, having judged the charger redeemed. The charger nuzzles your hand as the burdens of the past are lifted from the beast. You now feel as though you could call upon this beast to serve as your steed, should the need arise.$B$BYou have claimed your epic charger, $C! Congratulations!' WHERE entry=7647;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is most impressive work. It seems that as Grimand gets older, his craftsmanship continues to improve. That\'s quite the feat when his work was already some of the finest you\'d find anywhere when he made my barding back in the day.$B$BWhile this barding would be a fine addition to any normal steed, we are not dealing with such a mundane beast. You\'ll need this barding blessed by an appropriate source for it to be worthy of resting on a $C\'s charger. I\'ll hold onto it for you until then.' WHERE entry=7648;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, my boy.$B$B<Lorekeeper Lydros tears out a page from the book.>$B$BI am sure you can make use of this recipe.' WHERE entry=7649;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, my boy.$B$B<Lorekeeper Lydros tears out a page from the book.>$B$BI am sure you can make use of this recipe.' WHERE entry=7650;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, my boy.$B$B<Lorekeeper Lydros tears out a page from the book.>$B$BI am sure you can make use of this recipe.' WHERE entry=7651;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Aright, mister, I got a hot deal for ya.$B$BI\'m lookin\' to offload some of these here Imperial plate armor recipes and need someone willing to take on the burden. All I want in exchange is some thorium bars. Sound good?' WHERE entry=7652;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7653;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7654;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7655;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7656;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7657;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7658;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='A pleasure doin\' business with ya.$B$BAnd $N, wipe that look of disgust off yer face.' WHERE entry=7659;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Are you headed back into the Scholomance, $N? You\'ve already paid such a great price for the use of the Divination Scryer - perhaps you\'d like to take another one with you. With it, you\'d be able to face the perils of the Great Ossuary once more.$B$BBy all means, have it. You\'ve certainly earned it.' WHERE entry=7666;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Your generosity is unrivaled, $N. I thank you for your kindness.$B$BI will be able to finish my divination scryer now, and I should be able to fashion more without further need of diamonds... perhaps you would be interested in helping me in its use? It is for a most important task, I assure you... one that left unchecked could spell unmitigated disaster for the spirit realm!' WHERE entry=7667;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I am glad to see you $N.  I know that you have awaited word as to how to acquire your charger, and now that time has come.$B$BYou will be surely tested in many different ways, but most importantly in your willingness to rise above numerous obstacles thrust before you.  These are not done as a learning exercise - your stature is beyond simple educational tests.  You must save your future companion from the clutches of the evil you have spent your life fighting.$B$BTake heed, your time has come!' WHERE entry=7670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc2='If you bring me your white stallion, I\'ll trade you for one from the new herd. The new horse will be just as fast as your old one, but have a different look to it. You can look at the swift steeds here to see what it will look like.$B$BMUST PAY 500 Gold too....' WHERE entry=7677;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Hunter test quest' WHERE entry=7681;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc2='Hunter test quest2' WHERE entry=7682;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I never thunk I\'d be lookin\' at thish ugly mug again!$B$BHe acshually looksh better without the resht o\' him attached.$B$BHere\'s yer reward *hic*, $R.' WHERE entry=7701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! Those sleepy Dark Irons will head back to their homes in the Depths to get some rest, greatly slowing down the productivity of the Slag Pit.' WHERE entry=7702;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wow... you ARE da true $Gking:queen;! I never think I see this gauntlet in my life! It look like it got no mojo left anymore... maybe that creepy elf try and ruin gauntlet. Well, I say HAR HAR to him!$B$BLook - this mark on da gauntlet an old old OLD timey magic mark, older than da Gordok they say. Well, as Captain of da Gordok, we all learn one thing over and over - how to make mark come to life and give power back to gauntlet!$B$BI do it for you, $Gking:queen;! Here, take da gauntlet and rule FOREVER!' WHERE entry=7703;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is better than even I could have thought possible! The Chambermaid\'s magical pillow is mine! You better believe you\'re going to get a nice reward for this accomplishment, $N!' WHERE entry=7704;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Scrumdillyriffic!  These cores will keep me working for some time.  Add to that the benefit of there now being fewer elementals along the coast, and I might no longer cry myself to sleep at the prospect of having set up shop in perhaps the worst place imaginable!$B$BThank you, $N, for your efforts on my behalf.  While it certainly straps me financially to do this, allow me to show you some gratitude you may understand and appreciate... loot!' WHERE entry=7721;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='I hope you kicked his teeth in too, $N. Ragnaros knows, he deserved it.$B$BNow we can get down to business.' WHERE entry=7722;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ye\'re a good lad, ye are. I got ye a lil\' present fer yer troubles.' WHERE entry=7723;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Hansel sneezes.>$B$BI think I\'m gettin\' a cold. Damn this frigid climate!' WHERE entry=7724;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Inconceivably fantastical, $N!  You\'ve come through for me again, and for that I thank you.$B$BThank you!$B$BWhile you may find this coin to be a little less than you\'re accustomed to, rest assured your great deeds on the field of goblindom are echoing through the halls of power in the Steamwheedle Cartel.  Should you need something else to do, then by all means talk to me!' WHERE entry=7725;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Top notch, $N, top notch!  While the coin I give you might not be the most you\'ll ever receive for such work, rest assured my comrades in the Steamwheedle Cartel will hear about your efforts!$B$BIf you are looking for anything else to do, then let me know.  I can always use more elemental cores and such.' WHERE entry=7726;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Oh me achin\' feets.$B$BI figured since ye didn\'t have a luffa...' WHERE entry=7727;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Fantastic work! Now for your reward.' WHERE entry=7728;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='15.9 pounds! That may be a new record for blood and gut weight on apparel! Congratulations, $C!' WHERE entry=7729;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Well done, $C.  Though the extensiveness of the Zukk\'ash presence will not be thwarted with anything less than a full-scale invasion, you have bought us some time so we can devise a proper strategy.$B$BI will be sure to have these carapaces analyzed; we\'ll need to learn everything about them before we deal with what has unfortunately turned into a much larger issue than we had anticipated.' WHERE entry=7730;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Impressive, $C... most impressive!  If Stinglasher is indeed one of their strongest creatures, the study of the beast will prove to be quite valuable in time.  It\'s now my charge to make sure we defend ourselves long enough to take advantage of it.$B$BPlease accept this coin bounty as a token of the entire camp\'s thanks, $N.  Well done.' WHERE entry=7731;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Ah, I\'ve been expecting this.  These creatures you faced... they are an ancient threat that the Horde continues to choose to ignore.  Hadoken was wise to bring this - and you - to me.$B$BThe Zukk\'ash are nothing more than creatures called the silithid.  Some would think that they are a mindless nuisance, but let me assure you - they are a far, far worse threat than anything the Alliance could muster.$B$BIf you\'re willing and strong enough, I could use your aid in bringing this threat to light.' WHERE entry=7732;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent, excellent!  These are going to work out incredibly well - I can already tell that they\'re going to be much harder when properly cured.$B$BThanks again for your help $N.  Here - please take one of my latest creations.' WHERE entry=7733;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Excellent, excellent!  These are going to work out incredibly well - I can already tell that they\'re going to be much harder when properly cured.$B$BThanks again for your aid, $N.  Here - please take one of my latest creations.' WHERE entry=7734;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Incredible!  You may have found the granddaddy of all yeti hides with this!$B$BYou better believe I\'ll pay you for it.  I normally don\'t pay that much for a single hide, but I\'m pretty sure I can make something special from it.  Thanks for thinking of me on this, $N!' WHERE entry=7735;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc2='Let\'s not waste more of my precious time with jibber jabber, $N. It\'s time to focus on replenishing our dwindling fiery flux supply.$BWhat I\'m gonna need from you is the following:$B$B*2 Incendosaur scales.$B*4 Kingsblood.$B*1 Coal.$B$BI\'ll take all that you can offer!$BAnd you\'ll do it fast if you wanna get in good with the Brotherhood.',objectives_loc2='Deliver 2 Incendosaur Scales, 4 Kingsblood and one Coal to Master Smith Burninate.',offerrewardtext_loc2='There\'s always room for more fiery flux, junior. Keep it comin\'... unless I tell you to stop.' WHERE entry=7736;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Keep the residue pouring in!' WHERE entry=7737;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='This is an incredible find! I believe this is the finest yeti hide specimen I have ever seen!$B$BIndeed, this is certainly worthy of an appropriate bounty. I normally don\'t pay that much for a single hide, but I\'m confident I can make something special from it. Thanks for thinking of me on this, $N!' WHERE entry=7738;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You don\'t even flinch as the smoldering brand is pressed into your flesh. You are so tough!$B$BYou now hold the Mark of Drakkisath. Have fun storming the castle.' WHERE entry=7761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You need not be told the meaning of what you have done, $N. This day will be recorded in the annals of history. A victory the likes of which has not been known to the Alliance for years - if ever!' WHERE entry=7781;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Field Marshal Afrasiabi bows.>$B$BChoose your reward, let the celebration begin!' WHERE entry=7782;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='You have honored the Horde once more, $N. The son of Deathwing lays dead. Surely, the evil one stirs.' WHERE entry=7783;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Choose your reward so that I may mount the head of the beast for all to see.' WHERE entry=7784;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='May you be protected in your crusade. May the Master bless your efforts.' WHERE entry=7785;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Even in dreams I did not dare foresee this day.$B$BBehold, mortal.$B$BBEHOLD HE WHO IS OLDER THAN EXISTENCE!$B$BBEHOLD HE WHO HAS FACED TITAN AND GOD ALIKE!$B$BRISE MY MASTER! BREAK FROM YOUR BONDS!' WHERE entry=7786;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Please do not harm me! Take it! Take the blade! Leave Demitrian to reshape his pathetic life!' WHERE entry=7787;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='<Captain Shatterskull roars in triumph.>$B$BHow much more can they withstand? How many more Alliance filth must perish at the hands of the Horde for them to retreat? Only time will tell, $R.' WHERE entry=7789;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! We thank you for your generous donation, $N!' WHERE entry=7791;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! We thank you for your generous donation, $N!' WHERE entry=7792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! We thank you for your generous donation, $N!' WHERE entry=7793;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Wonderful! We thank you for your generous donation, $N!' WHERE entry=7794;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='Fantastic - these will go right to use, I assure you. Thank you again for your assistance! We\'d certainly be lost without you.$B$BWith all the donations you\'ve made, I would certainly process any additional runecloth donations you care to make in the future. Just be sure to check in with me, and I\'ll personally make sure that your good deeds won\'t go unrecognized!' WHERE entry=7795;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc2='$N - without heroes like you working on behalf of the tribe, we\'d surely suffer. Thank you for your continued efforts!' WHERE entry=7796;
